Run a single sync pass for one (database, target), regardless of the target's mode; prunes afterward when retention is set

Usage: sleet mirror sync [OPTIONS] <ROOT> <DB> <TARGET>

Arguments:
  <ROOT>
          Fleet root URL, e.g. s3://ops/sleet/

  <DB>
          Registered database URL

  <TARGET>
          Mirror target name

Options:
      --rclone <RCLONE>
          Path to the rclone binary, for targets with copier = "rclone"

      --format <FORMAT>
          Output format

          Possible values:
          - text: Human-readable text
          - json: JSON matching the subcommand's response schema
          
          [default: text]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
